 <center> 
  <h1><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Adaptive Hypermedia Application 
    Model (AHAM)</font></h1> 
 </center> 
 <p><br>
  <font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">How does AHAM fit in with the Dexter Hypertext Model?</font></p>
<ul>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">AHAM focuses on the storage layer 
    just as the Dexter model does</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">AHAM also concentrates on anchoring 
    and presentation specifications like the Dexter model</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">AHAM, however, extends the Dexter 
    Hypertext Model with hypermedia adaptation based on a <em>user model</em>, 
    a <em>domain model</em>, and <em>teaching model (a.k.a. adaptation model)</em></font></li>
</ul>
<p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Although the AHAM model uses the 
  term <em>teaching model</em>, it does not indicate that this model can only 
  be applied to educational hypermedia systems.</font> </p>
